Package com.github.mibac138.argparser.binder

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BindMethod  
    BoundMethod
    Represents a bound method. Can be easily invoked using invoke
    Index
    Annotation used to class CallableBoundMethod generate indexed syntax elements
    Name
    Annotation used to class CallableBoundMethod generate named syntax elements
    SyntaxGenerator
    Used by interface BoundMethods to generate syntax.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotationBasedSyntaxGenerator<T extends Annotation>
    A little convenience class. Does the param checking for you
    AutoIndexSyntaxGenerator
    Generates indexed syntax for elements which have neither interface Name nor interface Index annotations by using the auto index function
    BoundMethodKt  
    CallableBoundMethod
    Kotlin's reflection based bound method (works for Java too*)
    IndexKt  
    IndexSyntaxGenerator
    Generates indexed syntax by using the interface Index annotation
    JavaDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
    Basically a port of Kotlin's optional KParameters. When setting default values parsers should return them if they couldn't parse the input
    KotlinDefaultValueSyntaxGenerator
    Generates relevant syntax for optional KParameters
    MethodBinder
    Factory class for creating interface BoundMethod. This is the recommended way for most people to create their interface BoundMethod instances. Creating instances on your own is not advised
    MethodBinderKt  
    NameSyntaxGenerator
    Generates named syntax by using the interface Name annotation
    NullSyntaxGenerator
    Represents an empty interface SyntaxGenerator
    ParamNameSyntaxGenerator
    Generates syntax based on KParameter's name. Works as a last resort option (generates syntax (class NameComponent) only if it hasn't been already generated)
    SyntaxGeneratorContainer
    Syntax generator consisting of other generators. Does nothing on it's own. When running generate it invokes all of the added generators.
